                                                                                                               Tatas ink Japan deal
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Tata Capital managing director Praveen Kadle (left) with Mizohu Securities deputy president Shigeyoshi Nishiyama in Mumbai on Thursday. (PTI)                                   
	Mumbai, Feb. 15: Tata Capital, the wholly owned subsidiary of Tata Sons, has entered into an alliance with Japans Mizuho Securities to provide a wide range of financial services.        
	The duo will explore opportunities in private equity, investment banking, including cross border mergers and acquisitions, securities business, including broking and distribution, structured finance and wealth management.        
	Praveen P. Kadle, managing director of Tata Capital, said, We are pleased to explore business opportunities with Mizuho Securities and shall work towards strengthening synergies in our respective financial services businesses.         
	This will enable us to offer our clients sophisticated solutions for their investment and financial needs, Kadle said.        
	Mizuho deputy president Shigeyoshi Nishiyama said, This alliance with Tata Capital will provide significant potential for the expansion of our businesses in India.                                                                                                                                        
